Hello!

I am writing a quick little module to use the [Drupal Relation](https://www.drupal.org/project/relation) module.   The [Tripal Relation Module](https://github.com/bradfordcondon/tripal_relation) finds relation types that are between Tripal Entity and provides support for Chado-linking them to autogenerate relationships.  The result is you get "free" fields from the relation module to display related entities (all the biomaterials for an organism, all the analyses with a biomaterial, etc) if you can link them in Chado.


Unfortunately there is a hook naming problem.  The relation module defines this callback function: 

```
/**
 * Callback to create a relation.
 */
function relation_entity_create($values = array()) {
    $relation = relation_create($values['relation_type'], []);
    foreach ($values as $key => $value) {
      $relation->{$key} = $value;
    }
    return $relation;
}
```

This accidentally hooks into entity_create hook defined in `TripalEntityController`.

What's the best way for me to resolve this?  Maybe the Tripal hook could ignore the relation module?
